Notebook[{
Cell["The Stabilizer Formalism, by Computation", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"cbe7fbac-bdd5-4b64-a241-972b883e79ba"],

Cell["\<\
This document teaches the stabilizer formalism the way one would teach it at \
a chalkboard with a kernel open: every claim is immediately computed. We \
start from the observation that a single qubit can be specified not by its \
two amplitudes but by the one operator that fixes it, build that idea into \
the Aaronson-Gottesman tableau, and ride it all the way to thousand-qubit \
Clifford circuits, error-correcting codes, graph states, magic states, and \
Clifford channels. We close with a measured, honest comparison against the \
specialized C++ and Julia stabilizer simulators.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"86bb529f-f277-4a8a-a87a-344e0b667ed1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The arc is: a state is what stabilizes it (single qubit), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "980bbcf1-8c4b-47b0-8886-080a01bfd87d"],
 " generators replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2ab19ad3-fe50-4545-86a4-bbd799f8379c"],
 " amplitudes (the tableau), entanglement and measurement become linear \
algebra over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c9201911-7548-430c-889f-45578b4363a6"],
 ", and then scale, codes, and the frontier. The audience is graduate \
students who know quantum mechanics and the Pauli group but have not yet seen \
why a stabilizer state of a thousand qubits is something you can hold in your \
hand. Everything below is built explicitly so you can change it, break it, \
and extend it. The Wolfram QuantumFramework symbols we exercise live in the \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Wolfram"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "7b84bf6d-d6cb-4e3a-bd9a-f2baf3010859"],
 "QuantumFramework",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"`", " ", "paclet"}], ";", " ", 
   RowBox[{"the", " ", "central", " ", "one", " ", 
    RowBox[{"is", " ", "["}]}]}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bdeed863-bfcb-4315-a0c3-2cae4b90be9a"],
 "PauliStabilizer`]."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2172c0ad-ce39-4f83-bca9-40d065b63bf1"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"41518470-a269-4b9e-8139-f6ea0013407e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We load the framework from the working tree so the fast paths and recent \
fixes are present. On a current release, the plain ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Needs"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b8ea0fee-6485-4af5-9023-02a8ce0a971f"],
 " line alone suffices."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"07afc43f-2dbe-47e6-9a52-3cad96663ee3"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
  "PacletDirectoryLoad", 
   "[", "\"\</Users/mohammadb/Documents/GitHub/QuantumFramework/\
QuantumFramework\>\"", "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"2b751bf8-3e80-46ca-a9e9-4335cda0c524"],

Cell["The core functions at a glance", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"21740663-c2f8-44df-9960-fae597e0d945"],

Cell["\<\
Before the narrative, the whole working surface, grouped by task. Every call \
is exercised in context later; this is the map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3f4c1d37-2fd9-45f4-8647-4b05e5cc5c4b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Construct", "TI"],
 " a register, from signed Pauli strings, a named code, or a random Clifford: \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b7d0fb38-3a4c-4f0f-a725-6f6137d5507d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<XX\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"84f7027c-e5da-4389-849d-c52de4d99325"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "\"\<SteaneCode\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"f693c2ed-9e83-4457-8616-4f79c3780d50"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Random\>\"", "[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"78f48200-d127-4640-ab85-4836c2e24de2"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"77dbf542-fec2-4303-9306-44ceab2e42cf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a Clifford gate", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"32ba70ae-eb56-416f-9b9d-14c0ef0e245d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<S\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"6c2391ab-028a-4b41-bb43-0916fad6e7fb"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"3a34f562-c5c5-4e96-aee7-40057af22d5d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CZ\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"9a7fb4eb-7e91-459c-b2a6-7f716fd82371"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SWAP\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"2f8a5bec-345c-451c-8f56-7ff325579b12"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"c171c1da-1783-44a5-8d02-aaeacc9c3622"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Fold a whole circuit", "TI"],
 " in one compiled pass: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<ApplyCircuit\>\"", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], ",", " ", "..."}], "}"}]}], 
   "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "34e2f3ee-8061-41dd-8666-710eb2730b63"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"032b60ee-b4c4-43c6-bf87-e6c56c27c420"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Inspect", "TI"],
 ": ",
