 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0396bab7-dfd4-4b4b-9231-8497a2d814e8"],

Cell["Why stabilizers: the exponential wall", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b72b8c14-b722-425c-8bec-0bab6c388918"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure state of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2c61b279-7c03-4caf-93ce-162aeeaf3ef1"],
 " qubits is a unit vector in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\:2102", 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "82a630ba-078d-4fdf-8b89-78e28d3abe06"],
 ", so writing it down means storing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c8e699c5-7de6-462b-9746-b54f75d25191"],
 " complex amplitudes. At ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "20"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c3fd9e38-2327-4d92-a033-bb4d6ab27454"],
 " that is already a million numbers, at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "50"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "50593810-e51a-4a97-a96c-7616fbee797b"],
 " it exceeds the number of atoms in a building. Yet many of the states we \
care most about, including every state any error-correcting code protects, \
are not generic: they sit at the fixed points of a large group of Pauli \
operators, and that structure can be stored in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "16610d06-a969-4316-a391-e39e0fec50da"],
 " bits."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c4075ae2-d0e8-4c97-aae8-0f422593f57c"],

Cell["\<\
To feel the wall, ask for the dense state vector of a 20-qubit GHZ state and \
look only at its length:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"826016d8-5325-4b95-8c83-9d318c041d2a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Length", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "20", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"",
    "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"ecf7926b-0b11-4402-88b5-f4152c27ba62"],

Cell[BoxData["1048576"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"47f9560e-ac63-4bd6-8377-2d256a87950b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "That is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", "20"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "32a1b661-dc74-4a74-8e2b-5e51ce31eb7e"],
 " amplitudes for a state that, as we will see, is pinned down completely by \
20 short Pauli strings. The stabilizer formalism is the bookkeeping that \
exploits exactly this gap."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"23a53582-bd11-4a96-8ee1-22834b32dfd4"],

Cell["A state is what fixes it: the single qubit", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bf618b44-60ca-4f81-8c00-7c840d327c23"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The central move is to stop describing a state by its amplitudes and start \
describing it by the operators that leave it invariant. The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "92333820-cd58-4812-ad5d-2a12fa34746d"],
 " is the unique ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4a67f3eb-4104-45e2-b3da-165c367f8135"],
 " eigenvector of the Pauli operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d6e1e122-cde1-4127-a74d-9bcc19148d8e"],
 ". We say ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "856ce8e4-48a8-4fe8-97d3-19dec4c75eb6"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["stabilizes", "TI"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "af88521f-78a6-4ee4-aa78-4533bb993126"],
 ", and since one operator already determines a one-qubit state up to \
normalization, that single fact ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " the state."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0f559ff2-00f2-461a-973d-03e9032ab3a0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5fd45462-f790-4f47-96a7-8c854ea7f99c"],
 " fixes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6c534260-3723-42e8-bea8-67263fcbb552"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"26266a11-2ee6-4541-92cb-1892b0530327"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}], " ", "==", " ", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"59133ff9-60b6-4dfb-93fa-4d3113716744"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"c022b4bc-d003-4abf-8f1b-4cb1b42bf7c9"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the framework, the one-qubit register ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cfff9f3f-c535-4adc-9df2-d91ebcfca6e5"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "c4230217-3b5b-4ac8-97c8-641b1f5ed277"],
 ". The object prints as a summary box that shows its generators and, for \
small systems, its tableau, so the cheap representation is the thing you \
see:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5c1d7a31-4ea0-48ec-bb73-8017f7d96e45"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "1", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"2ecc54d2-f97c-4444-aade-98dcd879cee2"],

